Invocation Name: aetna health guide
Developer Terms of Use
des:
Let's face it: The health care system can be confusing. And a good chunk of that confusion lives in the complex terms and phrases used to actually get you the care you need. We're here to help change that. 

The AETNA HEALTH GUIDE ™ skill will help you make sense of health insurance terms, plan types and descriptions. Clear and simple. Plus, it'll give you answers to frequently asked questions about our resources and insurance plans. So you can spend less time with a dictionary and more time doing what you love.

Just ask Alexa to open AETNA HEALTH GUIDE ™. You can ask questions like:

• What is the difference between coinsurance and a deductible?
• How do I replace my ID card?
• Can you explain an EOB to me?

The AETNA HEALTH GUIDE ™ skill is always trying to learn and improve based on the questions you ask, in an effort to make your health care easier to understand. So check back often for updates! This is just one part of our mission, as a CVS Health® company, to help people on their path to better health.

Aetna offers health care insurance and related services nationwide through employer-paid insurance and benefit programs, and through Medicare. Our team of over 1.2 million health care professionals, 690,000 primary care doctors and specialists and 5,700 hospitals serve 22 million medical members.

[Disclaimer] 

This tool does not provide medical advice and is for informational and educational purposes only. AETNA HEALTH GUIDE ™ is not a substitute for professional medical advice, treatment or diagnosis and does not provide or store any personal health information. Call your doctor to receive medical advice. If you think you may have a medical emergency, please dial your local emergency response phone number.
